The Police in Katsina State said its men have rescued 10 out the 15 women kidnapped by bandits in the early hours of Tuesday in Wurma village, Kurfi Local Government Area of the state. The Public Relations Officer, ASP Anas Gezawa, on Wednesday in Katsina said: ”gunmen invaded Wurma village in Kurfi local government and abducted 15 women including the Village head’s daughter and his in-law”. Gezawa said the bandits also carted away an unspecified number of cattle from the community. “ The police team rescued 10 out of the 15 abducted women. They have since been reunited with their families. ”Effort are being intensified to rescue the other victims and possibly arrest the culprits,” Gezawa stated. (NAN) Police rescue 10 out of 15 women abducted in Katsina community ...abduct many women in Katsina village Bandits kill 17 in Katsina villages Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin